		<Id>1774600200001</Id>
		<Name><![CDATA[Calibrated]]></Name>
		<Description><![CDATA[Calibrated experiment with realistic service times (triangular distribution) and parameters tuned for a stable 2-worker equilibrium. Arrivals gated to open hours (6am–2pm, ~80/day at mean 6-min inter-arrival), service time triangular(2, 5, 8) min, mean=5 min. Reviews are enabled: multiplier range narrowed to 0.7–1.3 (±30%) to allow gentle wobble without destabilizing the 2-worker equilibrium. With avgWait ~5.5 min and threshold 10 min, most reviews are positive, so the multiplier trends toward 1.2–1.3 in steady state.]]></Description>
